Project goal:
Build a safe ACM LaTeX editing agent with three layers:
1. structural parser,
2. intent router,
3. surgical patch editor.

Architecture rules:
- The parser must build a tree of sections, environments, and protected regions.
- The router must map user requests to fixed intents only.
- The editor must patch only exact ranges and never regenerate the full document.
- Never modify ACM internals, template files, class/package files, or reference assets.
- Preserve labels, citations, comments, formatting, and protected LaTeX commands.
- Reparse after every successful write.
- Validate output before writing.
- Use session/workspace separation and per-workspace locking.
- Keep legacy Latex_Alignment code untouched unless explicitly migrating code into Latex_editor.
- Write tests for every parser, editor, router, and service change.

Coding style:
- Prefer small, deterministic functions.
- Keep business logic in usecases/services.
- Keep HTTP routes thin.
- Keep database access isolated.
- Keep ACM reference files read-only.
- Keep schema and history logic in the database layer.
- Add logging for exceptions and rejected edits.
